{{Documentation subpage}}
{{tsh|qref}}
{{Lua|Module:String}}
A Template to makes citations of the Quran, linking to pages of https://quran.com .
__FORCETOC__

== Usage ==
This template is used to provide reference of [[Āyah|Quran Verses]].

Basic Code format:
<code><nowiki>{{CiteQuran Ayah|SurahNumber|AyahNumber}}</nowiki></code>

::'''OR Shortcut'''

::::::<code><nowiki>{{qref|SurahNumber|AyahNumber}}</nowiki></code>

Advance Code format:
<code><nowiki>{{CiteQuran Ayah|SurahNumber|AyahNumber|b=y/yt|s=y|t=c/si|c=y}}</nowiki></code>

== Redirects ==
These are the redirects means we can also use these words to use this templete, e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|Qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl}} {{tlc|_show_result=yes|Qverse|2|256|b{{=}}yl}}
*{{t|Qref}}
*{{t|Qverse}}
*{{t|Citequran}}
*{{t|Quranverse}}
*{{t|Quranrange}}

== Optional parameters ==
<big>'''1. b'''</big>
:b, short-form of begin. It make the cite to begin cite with the word '''Quran'''.
:It has two value:
::*'''y''', short for ''yes'', To add and begin cite with the word Quran.  e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}y}}
::*'''yl''', short for ''yes with link'', To add and begin with the word Quran with link of word 'Quran' to its Wikipedia page. Avoid use of '''yl''' , more than once in a single article as per [[MOS:REPEATLINK]].
:::e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl}}

<big>'''2. s'''</big>
:s, short-form of Superscript. It add cites in superscript style.
:It has only one value, 
::'''y''' short for ''yes'' e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|s{{=}}y}} {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl|s{{=}}y}}

<big>'''3. c'''</big>
:c, short-form of Chapter (Surah). It add and begin cite with the Surah (Chapter) Name. There is no effect of '''s''' parameter on it. It is recommended to not use this together with '''b''' parameter.
:It has only one value, 
::'''y''' short for ''yes'' e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|c{{=}}y}}

<big>'''4. t'''</big>
:t, short-form of translation. It is use to add a specific translation, like ''[[The Clear Quran]], [[:en:Sahih International|Sahih International]], [[Tafhim-ul-Quran]]'' and translation of [[Muhammad Abdel-Haleem|Abdul Haleem]], [[The Meaning of the Glorious Koran|Pickthall]], [[The Holy Qur'an: Text, Translation and Commentary|Yusuf Ali]] and other popular Quran translations. Translation name will be always in superscript. 
::e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|t{{=}}c|b{{=}}yl}}
:It has following value.
::*'''c'''  for [[The Clear Quran]]
::*'''si''' for [[:en:Sahih International|Sahih International]]
::*'''tq''' for [[Tafhim-ul-Quran]]
::*'''h'''  for [[Muhammad Abdel-Haleem|Abdul Haleem]]
::*'''p'''  for [[The Meaning of the Glorious Koran|Pickthall]]
::*'''y'''  for [[The Holy Qur'an: Text, Translation and Commentary|Yusuf Ali]]
::*'''nq'''  for [[Noble Quran (Hilali–Khan)]]

<big>'''5. pl'''</big>
:pl, short-form of Plainlinks. It create link which is ''not'' followed by an [[Help:External link icons|external link icon]].
::e.g. {{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl|pl{{=}}y}}

==== Example ====
{|class="wikitable"
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2}}  {{Spaces|4}}<small>to cite entire Surah (chapter)</small>
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256-257}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}y|s{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl|s{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|c{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|t{{=}}p|b{{=}}yl|s{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|t{{=}}c|b{{=}}yl}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|t{{=}}si|b{{=}}yl}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|t{{=}}c|c{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|s{{=}}y|t{{=}}si|c{{=}}y}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|t{{=}}y|b{{=}}yl}}
|-
|{{tlc|_show_result=yes|qref|2|256|b{{=}}yl|pl{{=}}y}}
|}

==See also==
*{{t|Cite Quran}}
*{{t|CiteHadith}}
*{{t|Cite Tafsir}}

